-- Fulham Beats Stoke in Premier League as Schwarzer Saves Penalty
-- B y   B o b   B e n s c h
-- 2013-02-23T15:28:40Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-02-23/fulham-beats-stoke-in-premier-league-as-schwarzer-saves-penalty.html
Mark Schwarzer  saved a penalty kick
in the second half to help Fulham beat Stoke 1-0 in English
soccer’s Premier League.  Schwarzer dived to his right to stop  Jonathan Walters ’s
kick in the 56th minute at Craven Cottage after a handball call
against Ashkan Dejagah. Fulham took the lead in first-half
stoppage time as Dimitar Berbatov volleyed a shot past Asmir
Begovic.  The victory pulls Fulham within a point of 10th-place Stoke
and also moves the Cottagers nine points clear of the relegation
zone at the bottom of the standings.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Bob Bensch at 
 bbensch@bloomberg.net  